Every element uses values from the system. The result feels intentional and consistent.

Never deviate. If something doesn't feel right, go one step up or down. No "just a smidge more."

## Call the Spacing Police

- A spacing system is a short list of values. Use only those numbers.
- The 4-pixel grid is the standard. Stick to it.
- Audit your current work and swap off-system values. Your design will thank you.
